cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper deals with text document classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also investigates the performance impact of traditional machine learning and deep learning-based methodologies, which falls under the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses transfer learning, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV), and hence, it could also belong to the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision).
